      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like i've been walking for so long... just through this thick, grey fog. i kept thinking there was a destination, some kind of clearing or light at the end of the trail. but i've reached the edge. the path just stops here, right at the lip of a great, silent canyon. there's nothing left to walk on. it just feels so heavy... like the journey was never meant to go any further than this.",
