      "content": "but there is no new path. that's the thing. the fog isn't just thick, it's heavy, like it's pressing down on me, telling me there's nothing beyond this ledge. the trees have stopped, the ground is gone. it doesn't feel like a transition or a pause... it feels like the story is just finished. like the ink has run dry right at the edge of this cliff. i'm just so tired of trying to find a way to keep walking when the world itself has ended.",
